About Us
HERBIES THEN AND NOW
Herbie's has been a part of the Keys dining scene since the 1940's making it the oldest continually operated restaurant in Marathon! Originally named Maggie's Chowder House, it operated until the Konrath family purchased it in the 1950s, and was renamed Fishnet's Bar and Chowder House.  In 1963 the small but mighty restaurant began it's life as Herbie's. In 2014 the Demaras family combined their culinary arts to scratch cooking, craft beer, and smoked meats.
FAST-FORWARD TO 2023
We have the Herbie's of today keeping the tradition alive!
